rComments: One of the most knowledgeable and passionate about her field profs I've ever had. The lectures were so interesting and all the readings were available online except for a set of 3 comic books which are also really great (the assignments were based on the comics). You'll learn so much about the Métis in this course and about her own research!
teacherRatingTags: ['So many papers', 'Lecture heavy', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: This class was supposed to be about general unbiased geographical concepts about place, space, etc. instead,  she turned the entire course into a class about aboriginal studies. Coming out of it, I knew none of the concepts my peers did that took the class with other profs. Told us one thing for assigns, graded differently. Not approachable either.

She's such an understanding and reasonable person! She gave three (challenging) papers, and an in class final exam (which she gave to you on the last day of class). She's empathetic with late papers and really just wants to see you succeed. She is full of information and her lectures are enjoyable and informative. She doesn't post anything online.

Prof. MacDougall took an interesting perspective on Contested Places - having taken it in the past and dropped it, I was not looking forward to trying again, but her narrative lecture style and lack of readings really made the course stand out. Exams are fair, and she gives you detailed info on what to expect. 3 papers, each longer than the last

I loved professor MacDougall. She was extremely knowledgeable of the subject and exhibited immense passion for the subject. Although lectures aren't mandatory, she posts nothing online and there is no textbook. Therefore you really need to dedicate your time and energy to this course - which isn't hard because the material is fascinating!

Teaches the class about contested native spaces. She is passionate, but also gives different perspectives. First couple of lectures were boring, but then the subject material was great. She lectures with narratives which is nice. I learned a lot. No readings, but you pay close attention in class. Three papers and a very fair exams as assessment.

Her classes are very captivating and you will learn a lot, most likely while enjoying your time spent in the classroom. However, she is an extremely tough marker who appears to have little sympathy when docking grades. You may end up with a disappointing grade or two despite going to her office hours constantly & enormous amounts of effort.

I think I have a major intellectual crush on Professor MacDougall. She presents a complicated and diverse field of information in a manner that is extremely understandable and interesting. Her assignments are fascinating to complete. I have to actively stop myself from clapping at the end of every class with her. Cannot recommend her highly enough.

Professor MacDougall is an amazing lady!  She has high expectations, but that is ok - because her lectures are engaging, she wants you to succeed, and will do anything in her power to help you!  If you aren't afraid to ask for help, she will make sure you are set up for success. She is an amazing teacher, and an inspiration!
